Goya Social Club

  • goya_social_club_2.jpg
  • goya_social_club_3.jpg
  • goya_social_club.jpg

Description

Information

Inspired by the top clubs in Paris, London and Berlin, on weekend nights clubgoers at this venue in the heart of the neighbourhood of Salamanca can enjoy a varied range of house and techno music played by the best DJs on today's international scene.

Located in Calle Goya, with a capacity for up to 200 people, Goya Social Club is notable for its décor, a blend of industrial space and a certain clandestine air, as well as for the quality of its sound, its location and its exclusive atmosphere, which sets it apart from traditional night clubs.

Valet parking is available.

OUR SUGGESTIONS

Prado Museum

One of the world’s leading art galleries boasting works by Velázquez, Goya, El Greco, Titian, Rubens and Hieronymus Bosch, among others.

Thyssen-Bornemisza National Museum

Embark on a journey through seven centuries of European art, from the early 1200s to the late 20th century, taking in works by the likes of Dürer, Frans Hals, Gauguin, Van Gogh and Kirchner.
